hr.fer.zemris.java.tecaj.hw4.collections

Class SimpleHashtable

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.java.tecaj.hw4.collections.SimpleHashtable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<SimpleHashtable.TableEntry>

    public class SimpleHashtable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<SimpleHashtable.TableEntry>
    The SimpleHashtable class implements simple hash table collection. It has two public constructors, one without argument which creates table size of 16 slots, and another one with input number which creates table with size which is the nearest power of 2 to a given number.

    To keep a good performance, table can be dynamically reallocated and doubled its size. Only in that case, the complexity of method put() is bigger than O(1).

    If slot is consisted of an element and a new element get the same index as old, then elements from same slot are connected in singly linked list.

    Also, SimpleHashtable implements Iterable interface so it can be used in for each loops or it can create an iterator to iterate through the table.

    Version:
    1.0

      • put

        public void put(java.lang.Object key,
                java.lang.Object value)
        Puts a new element with specified key and value in hash table. If hash table already contains specified key, method only updates a value of an old element. Complexity of this method is O(1), but in case that by putting a new element table would reach an threshold, new table is created with doubled size.
        Parameters:
        key - Key of an element.
        value - Value of an element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If given key is null.
